                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2956/12.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bryan</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 336.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm my cable message of
                    this date as follows, and to report that the minister for foreign affairs to-day
                    corroborated what he told me at our last interview, stating that his colleague
                    of the war office has fulfilled the promise to release Francisco Freitas from
                    custody in Funchal.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Page Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
